  84     def _check_expected_dtype(self, obj, label):
  85         """
  86         Check whether obj has expected dtype depending on label
  87         considering not-supported dtypes
  88         """
  89         if isinstance(obj, pd.Index):
  90             if label == "bool":
  91                 assert obj.dtype == "object"
  92             else:
  93                 assert obj.dtype == label
  94         elif isinstance(obj, pd.Series):
  95             if label.startswith("period"):
  96                 assert obj.dtype == "Period[M]"
  97             else:
  98                 assert obj.dtype == label
  99         else:
 100             raise ValueError

 102     def test_dtypes(self):
 103         # to confirm test case covers intended dtypes
 104         for typ, vals in self.data.items():
 105             self._check_expected_dtype(pd.Index(vals), typ)
 106             self._check_expected_dtype(pd.Series(vals), typ)

 108     def test_concatlike_same_dtypes(self):
 109         # GH 13660
 110         for typ1, vals1 in self.data.items():
 111 
 112             vals2 = vals1
 113             vals3 = vals1
 114 
 115             if typ1 == "category":
 116                 exp_data = pd.Categorical(list(vals1) + list(vals2))
 117                 exp_data3 = pd.Categorical(list(vals1) + list(vals2) + list(vals3))
 118             else:
 119                 exp_data = vals1 + vals2
 120                 exp_data3 = vals1 + vals2 + vals3
 121 
 122             # ----- Index ----- #
 123 
 124             # index.append
 125             res = pd.Index(vals1).append(pd.Index(vals2))
 126             exp = pd.Index(exp_data)
 127             tm.assert_index_equal(res, exp)
 128 
 129             # 3 elements
 130             res = pd.Index(vals1).append([pd.Index(vals2), pd.Index(vals3)])
 131             exp = pd.Index(exp_data3)
 132             tm.assert_index_equal(res, exp)
 133 
 134             # index.append name mismatch
 135             i1 = pd.Index(vals1, name="x")
 136             i2 = pd.Index(vals2, name="y")
 137             res = i1.append(i2)
 138             exp = pd.Index(exp_data)
 139             tm.assert_index_equal(res, exp)
 140 
 141             # index.append name match
 142             i1 = pd.Index(vals1, name="x")
 143             i2 = pd.Index(vals2, name="x")
 144             res = i1.append(i2)
 145             exp = pd.Index(exp_data, name="x")
 146             tm.assert_index_equal(res, exp)
 147 
 148             # cannot append non-index
 149             with pytest.raises(TypeError, match="all inputs must be Index"):
 150                 pd.Index(vals1).append(vals2)
 151 
 152             with pytest.raises(TypeError, match="all inputs must be Index"):
 153                 pd.Index(vals1).append([pd.Index(vals2), vals3])
 154 
 155             # ----- Series ----- #
 156 
 157             # series.append
 158             res = pd.Series(vals1).append(pd.Series(vals2), ignore_index=True)
 159             exp = pd.Series(exp_data)
 160             tm.assert_series_equal(res, exp, check_index_type=True)
 161 
 162             # concat
 163             res = pd.concat([pd.Series(vals1), pd.Series(vals2)], ignore_index=True)
 164             tm.assert_series_equal(res, exp, check_index_type=True)
 165 
 166             # 3 elements
 167             res = pd.Series(vals1).append(
 168                 [pd.Series(vals2), pd.Series(vals3)], ignore_index=True
 169             )
 170             exp = pd.Series(exp_data3)
 171             tm.assert_series_equal(res, exp)
 172 
 173             res = pd.concat(
 174                 [pd.Series(vals1), pd.Series(vals2), pd.Series(vals3)],
 175                 ignore_index=True,
 176             )
 177             tm.assert_series_equal(res, exp)
 178 
 179             # name mismatch
 180             s1 = pd.Series(vals1, name="x")
 181             s2 = pd.Series(vals2, name="y")
 182             res = s1.append(s2, ignore_index=True)
 183             exp = pd.Series(exp_data)
 184             tm.assert_series_equal(res, exp, check_index_type=True)
 185 
 186             res = pd.concat([s1, s2], ignore_index=True)
 187             tm.assert_series_equal(res, exp, check_index_type=True)
 188 
 189             # name match
 190             s1 = pd.Series(vals1, name="x")
 191             s2 = pd.Series(vals2, name="x")
 192             res = s1.append(s2, ignore_index=True)
 193             exp = pd.Series(exp_data, name="x")
 194             tm.assert_series_equal(res, exp, check_index_type=True)
 195 
 196             res = pd.concat([s1, s2], ignore_index=True)
 197             tm.assert_series_equal(res, exp, check_index_type=True)
 198 
 199             # cannot append non-index
 200             msg = (
 201                 r"cannot concatenate object of type '.+'; "
 202                 "only Series and DataFrame objs are valid"
 203             )
 204             with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 205                 pd.Series(vals1).append(vals2)
 206 
 207             with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 208                 pd.Series(vals1).append([pd.Series(vals2), vals3])
 209 
 210             with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 211                 pd.concat([pd.Series(vals1), vals2])
 212 
 213             with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 214                 pd.concat([pd.Series(vals1), pd.Series(vals2), vals3])

 216     def test_concatlike_dtypes_coercion(self):
 217         # GH 13660
 218         for typ1, vals1 in self.data.items():
 219             for typ2, vals2 in self.data.items():
 220 
 221                 vals3 = vals2
 222 
 223                 # basically infer
 224                 exp_index_dtype = None
 225                 exp_series_dtype = None
 226 
 227                 if typ1 == typ2:
 228                     # same dtype is tested in test_concatlike_same_dtypes
 229                     continue
 230                 elif typ1 == "category" or typ2 == "category":
 231                     # TODO: suspicious
 232                     continue
 233 
 234                 # specify expected dtype
 235                 if typ1 == "bool" and typ2 in ("int64", "float64"):
 236                     # series coerces to numeric based on numpy rule
 237                     # index doesn't because bool is object dtype
 238                     exp_series_dtype = typ2
 239                 elif typ2 == "bool" and typ1 in ("int64", "float64"):
 240                     exp_series_dtype = typ1
 241                 elif (
 242                     typ1 == "datetime64[ns, US/Eastern]"
 243                     or typ2 == "datetime64[ns, US/Eastern]"
 244                     or typ1 == "timedelta64[ns]"
 245                     or typ2 == "timedelta64[ns]"
 246                 ):
 247                     exp_index_dtype = object
 248                     exp_series_dtype = object
 249 
 250                 exp_data = vals1 + vals2
 251                 exp_data3 = vals1 + vals2 + vals3
 252 
 253                 # ----- Index ----- #
 254 
 255                 # index.append
 256                 res = pd.Index(vals1).append(pd.Index(vals2))
 257                 exp = pd.Index(exp_data, dtype=exp_index_dtype)
 258                 tm.assert_index_equal(res, exp)
 259 
 260                 # 3 elements
 261                 res = pd.Index(vals1).append([pd.Index(vals2), pd.Index(vals3)])
 262                 exp = pd.Index(exp_data3, dtype=exp_index_dtype)
 263                 tm.assert_index_equal(res, exp)
 264 
 265                 # ----- Series ----- #
 266 
 267                 # series.append
 268                 res = pd.Series(vals1).append(pd.Series(vals2), ignore_index=True)
 269                 exp = pd.Series(exp_data, dtype=exp_series_dtype)
 270                 tm.assert_series_equal(res, exp, check_index_type=True)
 271 
 272                 # concat
 273                 res = pd.concat([pd.Series(vals1), pd.Series(vals2)], ignore_index=True)
 274                 tm.assert_series_equal(res, exp, check_index_type=True)
 275 
 276                 # 3 elements
 277                 res = pd.Series(vals1).append(
 278                     [pd.Series(vals2), pd.Series(vals3)], ignore_index=True
 279                 )
 280                 exp = pd.Series(exp_data3, dtype=exp_series_dtype)
 281                 tm.assert_series_equal(res, exp)
 282 
 283                 res = pd.concat(
 284                     [pd.Series(vals1), pd.Series(vals2), pd.Series(vals3)],
 285                     ignore_index=True,
 286                 )
 287                 tm.assert_series_equal(res, exp)

 289     def test_concatlike_common_coerce_to_pandas_object(self):
 290         # GH 13626
 291         # result must be Timestamp/Timedelta, not datetime.datetime/timedelta
 292         dti = pd.DatetimeIndex(["2011-01-01", "2011-01-02"])
 293         tdi = pd.TimedeltaIndex(["1 days", "2 days"])
 294 
 295         exp = pd.Index(
 296             [
 297                 pd.Timestamp("2011-01-01"),
 298                 pd.Timestamp("2011-01-02"),
 299                 pd.Timedelta("1 days"),
 300                 pd.Timedelta("2 days"),
 301             ]
 302         )
 303 
 304         res = dti.append(tdi)
 305         tm.assert_index_equal(res, exp)
 306         assert isinstance(res[0], pd.Timestamp)
 307         assert isinstance(res[-1], pd.Timedelta)
 308 
 309         dts = pd.Series(dti)
 310         tds = pd.Series(tdi)
 311         res = dts.append(tds)
 312         tm.assert_series_equal(res, pd.Series(exp, index=[0, 1, 0, 1]))
 313         assert isinstance(res.iloc[0], pd.Timestamp)
 314         assert isinstance(res.iloc[-1], pd.Timedelta)
 315 
 316         res = pd.concat([dts, tds])
 317         tm.assert_series_equal(res, pd.Series(exp, index=[0, 1, 0, 1]))
 318         assert isinstance(res.iloc[0], pd.Timestamp)
 319         assert isinstance(res.iloc[-1], pd.Timedelta)

 342     @pytest.mark.parametrize("tz", ["UTC", "US/Eastern", "Asia/Tokyo", "EST5EDT"])

 456     def test_concatlike_common_period_mixed_dt_to_object(self):
 457         # GH 13221

 459         pi1 = pd.PeriodIndex(["2011-01", "2011-02"], freq="M")
 460         tdi = pd.TimedeltaIndex(["1 days", "2 days"])
 461         exp = pd.Index(

 466                 pd.Timedelta("2 days"),

 475         tds = pd.Series(tdi)

 484             [
 485                 pd.Timedelta("1 days"),

 488                 pd.Period("2011-02", freq="M"),

 765         mixed_frame = float_frame.copy()
 766         mixed_frame["foo"] = "bar"
